## Current Task: Simplify Add System Form ✅ COMPLETED

### User Request:
User wanted to simplify the "Add System" form by:
- Removing the "Last Maintenance Date" field (not needed)
- Auto-calculating "Next Maintenance Date" based on installation date + maintenance schedule
- Making the calculation automatic when user selects installation date and maintenance frequency

### Solution Implemented:
[X] Added automatic next maintenance date calculation logic
[X] Removed "Last Maintenance Date" field from the form
[X] Made "Next Maintenance Date" field read-only and auto-calculated
[X] Added controlled state management for installation date and maintenance schedule
[X] Added useEffect hooks to recalculate date when inputs change
[X] Added special handling for "as-needed" maintenance (no scheduled date)
[X] Added form reset when modal closes

### Technical Implementation:

#### **1. Calculation Logic**:
- `calculateNextMaintenanceDate()` function handles all maintenance frequencies
- Weekly: +7 days from installation
- Monthly: +1 month from installation  
- Quarterly: +3 months from installation
- Semi-annual: +6 months from installation
- Annual: +1 year from installation
- As-needed: No automatic date (shows explanatory text)

#### **2. Form Improvements**:
- Removed "Last Maintenance Date" input field
- Made "Next Maintenance Date" read-only with gray styling
- Added "(Auto-calculated)" label for clarity
- Added placeholder text explaining the auto-calculation
- Special handling for "as-needed" maintenance with explanatory text

#### **3. State Management**:
- Added controlled inputs for installation date and maintenance schedule
- useEffect hook automatically recalculates next maintenance date
- Form resets when modal closes to prevent stale data

#### **4. User Experience**:
- **Simplified Form**: Removed unnecessary manual date entry
- **Automatic Calculation**: Users just select installation date and frequency
- **Clear Feedback**: Visual indicators show the field is auto-calculated
- **Smart Handling**: Different behavior for "as-needed" maintenance
- **Consistent Styling**: Maintains dark theme with proper contrast

### Benefits:
- **Reduced User Error**: No manual date calculation mistakes
- **Faster Data Entry**: One less field to fill manually
- **Consistent Logic**: Standardized maintenance scheduling
- **Better UX**: Clear visual feedback about auto-calculation
- **Flexible**: Handles all maintenance frequencies appropriately

